content.description:
Sit start with hand on the large flake.

Work your hand up the flake until a good crimp can be reached with the right.   Make a couple more pulls on sharp holds, and top out left of the overhanging block.
content.location: Left side of the South West Face.

content.description: Climb the somewhat chossy arete using surprisingly fun moves. Be circumspect of the rock near the top.
content.location: To the right of the China Doll climbs, on the arete around the corner.

content.description:
Sit start as for

Molly

.   Pull up and grab the good pocket out right.   From there work your way up onto the left curving arete.   Finish on good holds and top out at the finish of

Molly

.
content.location: North West face of the Molly Boulder

content.description: Climb the right of the two ribs on this boulder. The topout is slightly harder than the topout of China Doll.

Highly contrived, but good. Climb the wall left of Molly, starting at a right hand small pinch and left hand undercling (or lower with the left if desired), make a big move up to the right hand crimp and crank through to the lip. Avoid all the good pockets right of the crack feature.
content.location: The same wall as Molly, just to the left.

content.description: Use the two obvious good pockets around head height to make one huge move to the finishing jug of Molly. The grade is a filler, difficulty will be highly height- and dyno-ability-dependent.
content.protection: Pad, spot, you know the drill.
content.location: Right of the seam feature on the Molly Boulder.

content.description:
Sit-start on low pockets, make a couple easy moves in more pockets then stretch up high to the left-hand sidepull.  Pull up to the crimp in the horizontal seam or throw for the lip (crux).

Height-dependent
content.location: Molly Boulder, center of the northwest face - the highest point on the boulder.  Start just left of the block on the ground in front of the boulder.

content.description:
Sit start at a good incut hold.   Pull up into a tricep for your right, then reach through to an under cling for the left.

Reach over the overlap with the right to a small sharp side pull hold and then make a tricky sequence to get your feet high enough to launch for the jugs at the top.
content.location: Left side of the North West face of the boulder.

content.description: Starts on Head Heritage, tops out on the left instead of going straight up.
Exciting climbing on interesting features. Similar to China Doll, however, slightly more thought-provoking.
content.location: Southwest corner of the China Doll Boulder

content.description: Climb the pretty and inviting rib feature on the boulder left of Molly, on huge holds. Careful of some flaky rock at the top.
content.location: The tall rib feature on the boulder left of Molly.

content.description:
Sit start with your right hand on a good hold and the left on an undercling.    Pull up to the obvious sharp flake for the left then make a powerful sequence to gain the good sidepull high up for the right.

From here, finish direct, or slightly left.

Powerful for the grade.
content.location: Right side of the South West face.
